The previously headline empirical result that φ = 1/2 was overstated.
With the bug-fixed Runs A slow + Run C completed (L = 64–256 dense in λ,
plus L = 384 at λ = 0.05), the phase boundary λ_c(ζ) **does not** follow
the multicritical RG prediction λ_c ∝ √ζ. The current empirical picture
is summarised below; see `analysis/phase_diagram_v2.png` for the figure.

### Empirical phase boundary (from L=128 vs L=256 crossings where available, else L=64 vs L=128)

| ζ     | λ_c          | √ζ    | λ_c / √ζ |
|-------|--------------|-------|----------|
| 0.02  | 0.061 ± 0.007 | 0.141 | 0.43     |
| 0.05  | 0.178 ± 0.010 | 0.224 | 0.80     |
| 0.10  | 0.232 ± 0.016 | 0.316 | 0.73     |
| 0.20  | 0.430 ± 0.002 | 0.447 | 0.96     |
